        "client_msg_id": "61c9611c-986e-48a6-96ee-ef098b38f11b",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "I use writing tests for pretty much every role I hire for :slightly_smiling_face: It's hard to be a marketer and avoid writing!\n\nOne thing I have always found challenging with projects like the one Theresa described is that it's difficult to separate writing skill from industry knowledge. I frequently found myself reviewing the results and feeling like this person might be quite good and just didn't have the context on our space.\n\nSo I switched to \"tell me about a time you did X\" project. These types of projects put them on the strongest possible footing -- they're not guessing about my context, they're telling me about their context. It allows me to see:\n• Do they construct the story well?\n• Is the story compelling?\n• Did they understand their persona?\n• Did they understand the the business goals?\n• How did they collaborate with other folks on their team?\nIt's basically a behavioral interview in writing :slightly_smiling_face: And then I schedule time to go through the project with them and keep asking questions.\n\nI've found this to lead to really productive conversations that help me deeply understand their process, approach, and of course writing ability.",
